<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath" authorityName="Viraktamath" box="[730,1145,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis box="[730,999,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Japanagallia peculiaris</emphasis>
Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished from the latter by the symmetrical aedeagus with a slender ventral process directed dorsally and bifid apically, slender processes pointed dorsally at the midlength of the shaft on the ventral margin, and the shape of the pygofer lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1258,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,1258,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name alludes to the long slender ventral process of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
